{{cereal}}
[[Image:Zizania palustris macro.jpg|right|thumb|Wild rice grains]]

Despite the name, '''wild rice''' is not [[Cookbook:Rice|rice]]. It is a seed native to the Great Lakes region of North America. Compared to other grains, wild rice is highly nutritious. The seeds are purple-tinted black, 1/3 to 1/2 inch long, and about 1/16 to 1/8 inch in diameter.

{{Wikipedia|Wild rice}}

