'''Lady finger''' is an ambiguous term that can mean:
* [[Cookbook:Okra|Okra]], a green [[Cookbook:Vegetable|vegetable]] from [[Cookbook:African cuisines|Africa]]. * [[Cookbook:Savoiardi|Savoiardi]], a kind of small [[Cookbook:Sponge Cake|sponge cake]] from [[Cookbook:Cuisine of Italy|Italy]]. * In North America, "ladyfinger" typically refers to a more modernized, smaller, thinner cookie than the traditional savoiardi, from which its name is taken; the two are often used interchangeably, but are completely different in flavour and texture, with the newer more closely resembling uncoated chocolate fingers. * The "lady finger" [[Bartending/Cocktails|cocktail]].
"Lady finger" can also mean a type of firecracker or human body part, but these are generally very bad to eat.
{{Wikipedia|Lady finger}}

