==Integration by parts==
{{question-answer|question=14. Consider the integral <math>\int \sin(x) \cos(x)\,dx</math>. Find the integral in two different ways. (a) Integrate by parts with <math>u=\sin(x)</math> and <math> v' =\cos(x)</math>. (b) Integrate by parts with <math>u=\cos(x)</math> and <math> v' =\sin(x)</math>. Compare your answers. Are they the same?|answer={{noprint|a. <math>\frac{\sin^{2}x}{2}</math><br/>b. <math>-\frac{\cos^{2}x}{2}</math>}}}}
